summary:
The Public Intervention Project "GRU-111: Contracartografias" is part of the Project Contracondutas conducted by Escola da Cidade - originated from an action of the brazilian justice system within the actions of combat and eradication of labor analogous to slavery in the construction of Terminal 3 of Guarulhos International Airport, in 2013. GRU-111: Contracartografias takes the airport as object-icon of the contemporary context of mercadification and globalization to be interpreted and countercartographed; as an epicenter from which one can investigate broader correlations - but, articulated with the overall focus of the Project - between architecture, work, tourism, behavior, infrastructure, financialization, public and private, migrations, international trade, luxury, precarization, desires, exploration, control and flows, among others. The hypothesis is that it is possible to connect the existence of "labor analogous to slavery" to a larger universe of variables that construct the current context, and the airport, in particular.

